drjoliv.fjava.foldable

Interface Foldable<M extends Witness,A>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Functor<M,A>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Traversable<M,A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FList, FList.Cons, FList.Nil

    public interface Foldable<M extends Witness,A>
extends Functor<M,A>
    A data structure that can be folded. 
    
 F2<Integer,Integer,Integer> go = (i, ii) -> i + ii;
 FList<Integer> ints = range(0, 10);
 Integer sum = ints.foldr(go, 0)
 // sum == 45
 }
    Author:
    Desonte 'drjoliv' Jolivet : drjoliv@gmail.com
